WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.480
 Here is a problem that sounds simple but turns out to be one of the harder things in AI right

00:00:05.480 --> 00:00:06.580
 now.

00:00:06.580 --> 00:00:11.920
 You point an agent at your whole code base or your company's entire knowledge base.

00:00:11.920 --> 00:00:17.400
 That's millions of tokens far more than fits in this context window.

00:00:17.400 --> 00:00:22.400
 Then you ask one question and the answer lives in maybe three sentences buried somewhere

00:00:22.400 --> 00:00:23.820
 in all of that.

00:00:23.820 --> 00:00:27.400
 So how does the agent find those three sentences?

00:00:27.400 --> 00:00:33.240
 If it dumps everything in, it slows down, it costs more, and it actually gets less accurate

00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:35.320
 which we covered last time.

00:00:35.320 --> 00:00:37.520
 The real skill is the opposite.

00:00:37.520 --> 00:00:43.000
 Pulling in only the right context exactly when it's needed, that's retrieval.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:45.640
 And it's changed a lot recently.

00:00:45.640 --> 00:00:46.400
 Let's walk through it.

